                <head>196. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On July 20, general elections were held in Ceylon, resulting in a victory for the
                    Sri Lanka Freedom Party. On July 21, <persName corresp="#p_SD1"
                        >Senanayake</persName> resigned as Prime Minister and Governor General
                        <persName corresp="#p_GSOE1">Goonetilleke</persName> called on Mrs.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMS1">Sirimavo Bandaranaike</persName>, the head of
                    the SLFP and widow of the former Prime Minister, to form a new government. She
                    successfully formed a new government and announced the composition of her
                    cabinet on July 23.</p>
            </div>
